The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in England so far as at 16 August is 275,200 (488.9 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 12 August, there were 6,551 new confirmed cases (11.6 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 05 August, there were 5,227 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 25% (1324 extra cases).
